The paper deals with a machine learning problem of estimating a tensor-structured linear regression model with a scalar response variable and tensor-structured predictors. The proposed method involves a non-convex optimization program over the space of sparse, low Tucker-rank tensors. This work involves topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), signal processing (cs.SI), and computer vision (cs.CV).
